Homemade Ranch

Ingredients-

Base:

1. 240 g Sour Cream
2. 460 g Mayonnaise
3. 210 - 270 g Buttermilk, depending on desired thickness

Herbs and Seasonings:

1. 12 g Garlic Powder
2. 12 g Onion Powder
3. 2 g Dried Dill
4. 4 g Black Pepper
5. 12 g Salt
6. 8 g sugar
7. 12 g Fresh Dill, minced
8. 12 g Fresh Chives, minced
9. 10 g Fresh Parsley, minced

Acid and Boosters

1. 20 g Lemon Juice
2. 20 g White Vinegar
3. 20 g Worcestershire (Optional)

Instructions-

Preparation:

1.) In largest mixing bowl you have, mix mayo, sour cream, and buttermilk and whisk until thoroughly combined.
2.) In a separate bowl add in all herbs and seasonings and mix until thoroughly combined.
3.) In a glass measuring cup or glass add in all acid and boosters.

Mixing:
1.) Add herbs and seasonings to the base and gently fold in until herbs and seasonings are properly mixed throughout the base.
2.) Add acid and boosters to the mix and gently fold.
3.) Cover bowl with saran wrap and leave in fridge to marinate for at least one hour(way better overnight).
4.) Serve and Enjoy

Things to note -
1.) To make spicy add 10 g of Calabrian Chili Paste during the first step of the preparation section.
2.) If you are unsure how thick you want the ranch, start with just 210 g Buttermilk and combine it. Then add more until desired consistency.

