Hot Honey Sauce/Seasoning

Ingredients-

1. 4 cups Honey
2. 1/2 cup Frank's Red Hot or Hot Sauce of your choice
3. 1/4 cup Red Pepper Flakes
4. 2 tsp Cayenne Pepper
5. 2 tsp Salt
6. 2 tsp Vinegar Powder or Citric Acid
7. 2 tsp Garlic Powder
8. 2 tsp Chipotle Powder
9. 2 tsp Smoked Paprika
10. 2 tsp MSG (Optional)

Instructions-

Sauce Preparation:

1.) Warm honey in a sauce pan on low heat until honey is loose and thinner. (Keep heat low to prevent any carmelization or burning)
2.) Stir in hot sauce and all spices.
3.) Keep on low heat 7-10 minutes and stir occasionally and lightly.
4.) Take off the heat and let sit for 15-20 minutes.
5.) Strain liquid if you want it more mild but leave as is if okay with a spicier flavor.
6.) Ready to use hot honey sauce!

For Seasoning Powder:

1.) Preheat oven to 170 F.
2.) After sauce cooled completely, spread thinly across 2-3 baking sheets.
3.) Bake at 170 F for 5 hours with oven cracked open slightly for the last 3 hours. Rotating pans every 30 minutes.
4.) Take out of oven and let cool completely.
5.) Grind down into desired consistency.

Things to Note-
1.) Your goal in the oven is to evaporate all water and moisture without actually cooking the product.
2.) The oven being cracked to allow moisture to escape is essential to dehydrating it.
3.) When warming the honey, if it begins to bubble take it off the burner immediately and lower you heat, it needs to come up to heat very slowly.

